A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Howard County – Department of Fire and Rescue Services – Current and
3 Prospective Employee Medical Cannabis Use
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Howard County Department of Fire and Rescue
5 Services from taking certain adverse employment actions against an employee or
6 prospective employee solely because of the employee’s or prospective employee’s
7 authorized use of medical cannabis; authorizing the Department to prohibit an
8 employee from working while impaired by cannabis or using cannabis at a certain
9 time; and generally relating to the Howard County Department of Fire and Rescue
10 Services.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Public Safety
13 Section 7–405
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Public Safety
19 7–405.
20 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “DEPARTMENT” MEANS THE HOWARD COUNTY
21 DEPARTMENT OF FIRE AND RESCUE SERVICES.
22 (B) THE DEPARTMENT MAY NOT FAIL OR REFUSE TO HIRE, DISCHARGE, OR
23 OTHERWISE DISCRIMINATE AGAINST AN INDIVIDUAL WITH RESPECT TO THE
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
