2 SENATE BILL 969
1 INDIVIDUAL’S COMPENSATION, TERMS, CONDITIONS, OR PRIVILEGES OF
2 EMPLOYMENT SOLELY BECAUSE THE INDIVIDUAL IS:
3 (1) A QUALIFYING PATIENT UNDER TITLE 36, SUBTITLE 3 OF THE
4 ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES AND CANNABIS ARTICLE; OR
5 (2) AUTHORIZED TO USE MEDICAL CANNABIS UNDER THE LAWS OF
6 ANOTHER STATE.
7 (C) THE DEPARTMENT MAY PROHIBIT AN EMPLOYEE FROM:
8 (1) PERFORMING THE EMPLOYEE’S DUTIES WHILE IMPAIRED BY
9 CANNABIS; OR
10 (2) USING CANNABIS WITHIN THE 12 HOURS IMMEDIATELY
11 PRECEDING THE EMPLOYEE’S SHIFT.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
13 October 1, 2025.

